Barcelona Retakes Lead Over Manchester Utd 2-1 in Champions League Final

-- B y   C h r i s   E l s e r
-- 
2011-05-28T20:01:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-28/barcelona-retakes-lead-over-manchester-utd-2-1-in-champions-league-final.html
Lionel Messi scored in the 54th
minute to give Barcelona a 2-1 lead over  Manchester United  in
the second half of soccer’s Champions League final.  The left-footed shot was the Argentine’s 12th goal in 13
matches. United had tied the match in the 34th minute on  Wayne
Rooney ’s strike at  London ’s Wembley Stadium.  Rooney exchanged passes with Ryan Giggs, getting the ball
back just inside the Spanish champion’s penalty area and curling
a shot into the net. Barcelona had taken a 1-0 lead in the 27th
minute when Pedro Rodriguez struck a right-footed effort past
United goalkeeper Edwin van der Sar.  After the first 30 minutes, Barcelona had 66 percent of the
possession, and had completed 265 passes to United’s 100. The
English champion used long passes and counter attacks to get
back in the match.  The winner will claim its fourth European title.  United coach  Alex Ferguson  decided not to include striker
Dimitar Berbatov in the squad, using Michael Owen on the bench
instead, while Barcelona’s Pep Guardiola kept defender Carles
Puyol among his subs. Berbatov had 21 goals in England’s Premier
League this season, tying him as top scorer with Manchester  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
